column5: Some good fishing and a nice PB laker Jacques.  Haven't had luck with the Macho on lakers, just the eyes.  Paul's always getting into quality bass too.  Good to see ya enjoying the summer.
Lots of nice quality fish there Jacques.  All day fishing with a buddy is the best.
Some quality fish there guys. Some nice quiet water there too! Thanks for posting that.
tres bien; some beauty fish there. congrats on the PB
Dang will not open on my phone. Sounds like a great time congrats on the new PB
Congrats on the PB, Jacques!!  Some really nice bass too.  Glad to see you getting out, and, having a blast!
Congrats on the PB Jacques!!  Some great looking bass in the videos as well.  Thanks for the report!!

Thanks Drew!!!  That laker was the first fish of the day... 5 - 10 min work out after arriving on the spot and it was FISH ON!!!  Gave me a great fight   bull dogging, gator roll and drag peeling was some of the highlights in this 15 min fight    Good thing I had spooled my reel with 14LBS mono the night before and Paul brought his Frabril musky size net    Couldn't imagine using my regular one I have for this brute.   Thanks Eric!!!  You bet   Thanks Roy!!!  Both days the wind was constant and had a good chop   Thanks Rick!!!   It was indeed a super time   Thanks Mike!!!   Thanks Frankie!!! 40 - 50 bass day of all sizes was what we experienced   Thanks Will!!!
Nice stuff Jacques!  Thanks for posting.  Your infectious enthusiasm is missed when you are away for too long.  Cheers, Mark
another great outing. Hopefully it isn't too long until your next!

Thanks Chad!!!  These 2 outings were the only ones of the summer for me... kind of had to leave trout to themselves since they didn't want to come out & play too much    Hoping to go out a couple more times in the near futur   Enjoyed both times out for sure   Thanks Doug!!!  Glad you like them
Just say when Paul, and I'm in    Round 2 sounds real good    Nice bucket!!  Is that a 6lbs'er??
